Moped is meant to be installed using a repository package, but if you are
installing it into a home directory or if you are making the package yourself,
then you need to know that the dependancies of Moped are:

Dependancies
    python > 3.0
    mpd

Optional Dependancies
    zenity     for a gui user input and feedback

To install, edit install.example and save it as install.sh, or provide your
own installation script. The default one can be renamed and it will run
correctly with package creation in Arch Linux.

Destination
    /usr/lib/moped/
    /usr/share/man/man1/

Optional Files and Folders
    roadmap/
    BUGS
    LICENSE (because it is GPL)
    install.sh
